Meeru draw.io lo MSIL Network Architecture ki sambandhinchina diagrams ni create cheyadaniki, kindha unna prompts ni upayoginchavachhu. Meeru draw.io lo unna "AI generation" feature ni vaduthunnaru kabatti, ee prompts chala clear ga panichesthayi:
1. Hub and Spoke Model Diagram kosam Prompt:
"Generate an AWS network diagram showing a 'Hub and Spoke' model. Include one 'Hub Account' in the center containing a Transit Gateway and a Firewall. Connect this Hub to three separate 'Spoke Accounts' (labeled Dev, UAT, and Production) using Transit Gateway attachments. Show VPCs inside each Spoke Account."
2. Firewall Placement & Traffic Flow Diagram kosam Prompt:
"Create a detailed AWS architecture diagram showing traffic flow. Start with a User hitting Route 53, then a Public Application Load Balancer (ALB) in a Networking Account. Show the traffic passing through a VM-Series Firewall (using Gateway Load Balancer - GWLB). After inspection, show the traffic going through a Transit Gateway to reach a Private ALB in an Application Account, which finally connects to EC2 instances."
3. Transit Gateway Peering (Global/Regional) kosam Prompt:
"Generate a diagram showing a central 'Transit Gateway (Mumbai)'. Show it connected to three other Transit Gateways via 'TGW Peering' (labels: Singapore Mulesoft, APIM Naggro, Xane AI). On the other side, show the Mumbai TGW connected to three VPCs via 'TGW Attachment' (labels: Dev Environment, Uat Environment, Prod Environment)."
4. Internal Maruti Network Hosting (DNS Flow) kosam Prompt:
"Create a sequence-style network flow diagram for internal Maruti network hosting. The flow should be: Internal User Browser -> Internal DNS/Route 53 -> Internal Public ALB (Networking Account) -> Firewall (DNAT & Inspect) -> Transit Gateway -> Private ALB (Application Account) -> App Compute (EKS/EC2)."
Draw.io lo tips:
Meeru prompt ichhaka diagram generate avuthundhi.
Adhi generate ayyaka, meeru manual ga icons (AWS logos) ni marchukovachhu ledha names ni double click chesi edit cheyavachhu.
MSIL specific names (like MSIL-PA-PUBLIC-ALB-01) ni labels ga add cheyandi.